Statements: c-jun negatively regulates the expression of pten by binding to the activator protein 1 site of the pten promoter, resulting in the concomitant activation of the akt pathway.

however, we show here that impaired tcr signaling via loss of itk also leads to a negative feedback loop in which defective repression of pten prevents downstream activation of pi3k- and mtor mediated pathways not just from the tcr, but from multiple cellular inputs.
